# Trinity Protocol v3.3.1 — UCI Data Integration

Upgrade the heart disease prediction model to incorporate a large UCI dataset and fix encoding issues to allow training on additional samples.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The UCI dataset uses different string labels (e.g., "typical angina" vs "TA"). I am implementing a mapping layer to ensure compatibility with the competition data.

## Proposed Changes

### [heart_top5_v3_2_elite.py](file:///home/kizabgd/heart_top5_v3_2_elite.py)

#### [MODIFY]
- **UCI Integration**: Add `load_uci_data()` to ingest and map `/content/heart_disease_uci.csv`.
- **Feature Schema Alignment**: Ensure columns like `Sex`, `ChestPainType`, `RestingECG`, `ExerciseAngina`, and `ST_Slope` are mapped consistently between UCI and S6E2.
- **Categorical Encoding**: Implement a final `LabelEncoder` pass across all categorical columns to allow `np.float32` conversion required for model input.
- **Training Expansion**: Append processed UCI data to the competition `train` set.

